      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, my apologies! I didn't mean to confuse you with my... *associates*. Honestly, sometimes my brain just defaults to the chaotic energy of a poorly organized goblin raid. Yes, when protein is high, you are generally correct to look for lower carbohydrates if weight management is your primary concern. High-quality protein is satiating, which helps your senior lab feel fuller longer, much like a well-fed, slightly suspicious goblin who is too full to raid the pantry.\n\nThink of it this way: protein keeps things solid, while excessive carbs can lead to that sluggish, round-belly look we try to avoid. You want the energy from the protein and healthy fats to keep him going, not the quick sugar rush that leads to a mid-afternoon nap under a toadstool—which is what some of the younger, less disciplined goblins do. If the food is packed with lean muscle builders, you're setting him up for steady, strong energy.\n\nBut don't completely eliminate carbs, as some complex carbs are fantastic fuel! It's not about cutting them out entirely, but rather choosing *smart* carbs. Look for sources like pumpkin or sweet potato over simple grains. If you see high amounts",
